# Repository policy

## Pull requests

- Never open a pull request unless the user explicitly asks for one.
- Never push a branch intended for automatic review by Cursor Bugbot or cloud agents.
- Do all work locally; the user merges when they choose.

## Git attribution

- Never add `Co-authored-by: Cursor`, `Co-authored-by: Cursor Agent`, `cursoragent@cursor.com`, or similar trailers.
- Never add `Made-with: Cursor` or other Cursor/Bugbot attribution to commits or PR descriptions.
- Commits should reflect the user's authorship only. Do not sign or attribute work to Cursor or cursor[bot].

## Dependencies

- Do not open Dependabot-style PRs for dependency bumps.
- When a dependency update is needed, apply the bump directly in the working tree and verify with build/tests.
